Source Foundation
This skill synthesizes principles from three sources:

"How to Design High Converting Emails For Ecom Brands in 2026" — Walshy Mails / Sunlo Consulting Contributed: copy frameworks (AID, PAS, Story), mobile-first design rules, Klaviyo export workflow, don'ts list, font/color discipline, Figma layout methodology.
"Watch me create a high-converting email design in 19 minutes" — Aaron Bermingham (Wellcopy) Contributed: asset extraction via DevTools, reverse-engineering winners from Milled.com, hero composition in high-resolution, visual hierarchy execution, trust signal placement before CTA, premium lifestyle aesthetic principles.
"How To Design Ecommerce Emails That ACTUALLY Convert" — Max Sturtevant (Wellcopy) Contributed: the three core conversion pillars (Ease of Click, Skimmability, Fluidity), before/after case studies (Yeti, Rise, Fenty Beauty, Peloton), per-product individual CTA buttons, infographic vs. paragraph copy, urgency/exclusivity signals, Klaviyo-native build workflow using drag-and-drop blocks and custom HTML, stripping distracting navigation from promotional emails, fluidity through background alternation and spacer blocks.
Combined, these three perspectives form a complete end-to-end system for building emails that convert in 2026 — from strategy through copy through design through Klaviyo build through QA.
